ElemRV
======

Fully Open Source RISC-V Microcontroller written in SpinalHDL. The chip layout was done with the IHP SG13G2 PDK and the open RTL-to-GDSII tool OpenROAD.

Installation
############

- Download and build all components::

	chmod +x init.sh
	./init.sh

ASIC Flow
#########

Create a layout from the Verilog file.

.. code-block:: text

    sg13g2-synthesize

Please check Known Issues in case the chip layout failed.

Finally, open the chip layout and inspect the layout.

.. code-block:: text

    sg13g2-gui

Docker
######

Custom Image
************

A Docker Compose configuration is provided for systems that do not run with the recommended
versions. The Docker will have included all required packages for the SDK, except vendor toolchains.
Build the image (which can take some minutes).

.. code-block:: text

    docker-compose build

Next, start the Docker in the background.

.. code-block:: text

    docker-compose up -d

Afterwards, west can be used identical to the CLI.

.. code-block:: text

    sudo docker exec -it ElemRV_1 make sg13g2-synthesize
    sudo docker exec -it ElemRV_1 make sg13g2-gui

Finally, stop the Docker.

.. code-block:: text

    docker-compose stop

Known Issues
############

No known issues so far.

